<latemp_subject "Verifying Solutions of Solitaire Games Automatically" />

<p>
<b>Games-Solitaire-Verify</b> is a <a href="http://www.cpan.org/">CPAN 
(Comprehensive Perl Archive Network)</a> module for verifying solutions of
Solitaire games. It was designed to serve as an aid in the test suite of
Freecell Solver, but may prove useful in other contexts.
</p>

<h2 id="download">Download</h2>

<ul>

<li>
<a href="http://search.cpan.org/dist/Games-Solitaire-Verify/"><b>Latest 
Stable Version on CPAN</b></a> - includes online documentation.
</li>

<li>
<a href="http://cpan.uwinnipeg.ca/dist/Games-Solitaire-Verify">Games-Solitaire-Verify on Kobesearch</a> (an alternative CPAN interface).
</li>

<li>
<a href="http://svn.berlios.de/svnroot/repos/fc-solve/trunk/Games-Solitaire-Verify/">Subversion 
Repository trunk</a>.
</li>

</ul>

<h2 id="features">Features and Limitations</h2>

<ul>

<li>
Modular design for implementing game variants - supports most of the 
variants supported by Freecell Solver.
</li>

<li>
Input and output are compatible with that of Freecell Solver's
<tt>-p -t -sam</tt> output (including several quirks).
</li>

<li>
Can handle the verification of individual cards, columns, entire states 
(= board layouts), moves and entire solutions.
</li>

</ul>

